Practice Area: Corporate/M&A, commercial transactions   

•	Represented foreign and local entities/VC funds with respect to M&A, asset-deal and local JV transactions in various sectors including biotech, retail trading, automotive, electronics and other; 

•	Lead the team of 10+ lawyers in all stages of the project (transaction structuring, LOI, DD, negotiation of the transaction terms, drafting the transaction documents, transaction closing and post-closing issues); 

•	Developed the strategy of the Russian market exits considering recent Russian counter-sanctions restrictions and EU/US sanctions regime;  

•	Coordinated external legal counsels (GB, Cyprus, etc.)  in connection with the respective foreign law issues in cross-border deals.

DENTONS / SALANS                                                     

PARTNER (2007 – June 2017); Counsel (2006 - 2007); Associate (1998 - 2006) 
Practice Area: Corporate/M&A         	 

• Represented foreign and local entities/VC and PE funds with respect to M&A, asset-deal and local JV transactions (incl. English law governed), market entry/exit in various sectors of Russian economy; lead the team of 10+ lawyers (incl. in other jurisdictions) in all stages of the projects;

• Advised client on the Russian law issues for the IPO project of master franchisee of the global food retail brand, resulting in offering raising approximately $120 million jointly with Dentons’ London and Istanbul office teams;

• Assisted Russian entities and local investment funds in their foreign investment projects abroad including EU countries and the US; coordinated external legal counsels in connection with the respective foreign law issues and regulations;

• Led one of the first automotive assembly greenfield projects in Russia; represented foreign investors in negotiations with the Russian state and regional authorities in relation to the investment agreements (projects included foreign investments up to $200 million);

• Assisted Russian high-tech entities in their foreign investment projects abroad including European countries and in the US;

• Represented clients in bankruptcy (including major cross-border bankruptcy cases), business restructuring and reorganization matters.
